  <h3>Will it look real in my slides?</h3>
  <p>
    The mockup reproduces the ChatGPT interface closely — prompt bubbles, response action icons, spacing and light/dark theme. At normal viewing sizes it's hard to tell apart from a genuine screenshot, which is exactly why the next section matters.
  </p>

  <h2 id="ethics">Use it responsibly</h2>
  <p>
    Fake AI screenshots are for <strong>clearly illustrative</strong> uses: slide decks, demos, tutorials, UI mockups and content. Don't use them to misrepresent what an AI actually said, fabricate evidence, or spread misinformation — that can be genuinely harmful, and it's the reason the export asks you to confirm your conversation is fictional. If there's any chance someone takes your mockup as a real AI answer, label it as simulated. Easy Chat Maker is an independent tool and is not affiliated with OpenAI, Anthropic or Google; interface styles are recreated for illustration only.
  </p>

